quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
11,54,"All we can say is that some god of ours has afflicted you with evil. {1} .Hud said: 'Indeed I take Allah as my witness, {2} and you too to be my witnesses that I have nothing to do {3} with your associating with Allah",footnotes:1:That is
11,55,"others than Him in His divinity. So conspire against me, all of you, and give me no respite. {1}",footnotes:1:This is his answer to their threat: “Some of our gods have smitten you with some evil” Compare this with (Surah Younus
11,56,"I have put my trust in Allah, Who is my Lord and your Lord. There is no moving creature which He does not hold by its forelock. Surely, My Lord is on the straight path. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
11,57,"If you, then, turn away (from the truth), know that I have delivered the message with which I was sent to you. Now my Lord will set up another people in place of you and you shall in no way be able to harm Him. {1} Surely my Lord keeps a watch over everything.'",footnotes:1:This is his answer to their obdurate denial: “Nor will we believe in you.”
11,58,"And when Our com-mand came to pass, We delivered Hud, together with those who shared his faith, out of special mercy from Us. We delivered them from a woeful chastisement."
11,59,"Such were 'Ad. They repudiated the signs of their Lord, disobeyed His Messengers, {1} and followed the bidding of every tyrannical enemy of the truth.",footnotes:1:Though only one Messenger had come to them
11,60,"They were pursued by a curse in this world, and so will they be on the Day of Judgement .Lo! 'Ad disbelieved in the Lord. Lo! ruined are 'Ad, the people of Hud."
11,61,"And to Thamud We sent their brother Sali'h. {1} He said: 'My people! Serve Allah; you have no god other than Him. He brought you into being out of the earth, and has made you dwell in it. {2} So ask Him to forgive you, and do turn towards Him in repentance. {3} Indeed My Lord is near, responsive to prayers . {4}",footnotes:1:This is the proof of the claim: “You have no other Deity than Allah” .The argument is based on the fact which the mushriks themselves acknowledged that it is Allah Who is their Creator. Therefore Prophet Salih (peace be upon him) argued like this: You yourselves acknowledge that it is Allah Who has created your wonderful human body out of the lifeless particles of the earth and that it is Allah Who has made the earth a suitable place for you to live. How can then there be any Deity other than Allah Who may be worthy of Godhead
11,62,"They said: 'O Salih! Until now you were one of those among us on whom we placed great hopes. {1} Now, would you forbid us to worship what our forefathers were wont to worship? {2} Indeed we are in disquieting doubt about what you are calling us to. {3}",footnotes:1:That is
